name: Global X Enhanced S&P 500 Index ETF
longDescription: USSL seeks to replicate, to the extent reasonably possible and net of expenses, 1.25 times (125%) the performance of an index of equity securities representing the large-cap market segment of the U.S. equity market (currently, the S&P 500 Index). USSL will use leverage in order to seek to achieve its investment objective. Leverage will be created through the use of cash borrowings or as otherwise permitted under applicable securities legislation. Designed to augment the growth potential of a diversified portfolio, USSL captures approximately 8 of available U.S. market capitalization.
